scenes.title: recursive tau-grid
scenes.content:
This grid was constructed by applying the "tau-divide" tool to the edge of the large square, using a consistent orientation, iteratively.

Clearly the grid contains the projections of all the vertices of the uniform blue polytope and its chiral alternation.

scenes.title: perspective
scenes.content: It is easy to convince yourself that all the polyhedron vertices lie on the grid points.
